00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,919
previously on Dumbgeons and Dragons.

2
00:00:01,919 --> 00:00:04,600
Shoot it at whatever you're shooting it at.

3
00:00:04,600 --> 00:00:05,440
Sorry.

4
00:00:05,440 --> 00:00:06,259
Dragon.

5
00:00:06,259 --> 00:00:10,279
When you use it, it adds an extra 60, 10 piercing damage.

6
00:00:10,279 --> 00:00:11,120
Whoa!

7
00:00:11,120 --> 00:00:11,960
Wowzer.

8
00:00:11,960 --> 00:00:12,780
What?

9
00:00:12,780 --> 00:00:17,780
You hear from all around you a voice say,

10
00:00:18,320 --> 00:00:22,359
it looks like the humans have brought me dinner.

11
00:00:22,359 --> 00:00:25,280
We want to dispatch of this dragon as quickly as possible

12
00:00:25,280 --> 00:00:28,800
so I should try and hit him with my magic arrow, right?

13
00:00:28,800 --> 00:00:29,640
Totally.

14
00:00:30,480 --> 00:00:32,000
Do we want to like save that

15
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:33,399
and really surprise him with it?

16
00:00:33,399 --> 00:00:34,780
Well, sure.

17
00:00:35,679 --> 00:00:39,120
She shoots it off and it deflects off of the scales.

18
00:00:39,120 --> 00:00:40,679
What?

19
00:00:40,679 --> 00:00:43,880
I'm trying to save some of my magic for later.

20
00:00:43,880 --> 00:00:46,100
And I piss myself.

21
00:00:48,840 --> 00:00:51,079
Friends, it's been nice knowing you.

22
00:00:51,079 --> 00:00:51,920
Yeah, it's been good.

23
00:00:51,920 --> 00:00:53,640
Same here, I think we may have all just died.

24
00:00:53,640 --> 00:00:55,600
I can't wait till I get to DM a campaign

25
00:00:55,600 --> 00:00:57,480
and murder Russ immediately.

26
00:00:57,480 --> 00:00:58,760
Have you been whispering like-

27
00:00:58,759 --> 00:00:59,919
Oh, sweet nothings.

28
00:00:59,919 --> 00:01:01,239
Sweet nothings in his ear.

29
00:01:01,239 --> 00:01:04,000
Like really break him down, just, you know.

30
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:08,679
Like, yeah, psychologically torment that fucking dragon.

31
00:01:08,679 --> 00:01:11,159
A crit 20, a match 20.

32
00:01:11,159 --> 00:01:12,000
What?

33
00:01:13,120 --> 00:01:14,319
Oh my God.

34
00:01:14,319 --> 00:01:16,200
I told you I believed in you.

35
00:01:16,200 --> 00:01:17,400
Amy, you're amazing.

36
00:01:17,400 --> 00:01:18,239
Wow.

37
00:01:18,239 --> 00:01:20,120
Thanks for believing in me, you guys.

38
00:01:20,120 --> 00:01:21,759
Can I just say that I am invisible

39
00:01:21,759 --> 00:01:23,400
and all I have done this whole time

40
00:01:23,400 --> 00:01:25,479
is stand up and get knocked down.

41
00:01:25,479 --> 00:01:27,359
I'll call you chumbalumpa.

42
00:01:27,359 --> 00:01:30,040
He has recharged his breath weapon.

43
00:01:30,040 --> 00:01:31,280
19.

44
00:01:31,280 --> 00:01:34,359
Constitution is plus one, so that is an eight.

45
00:01:34,359 --> 00:01:36,359
Record scratch, freeze frame.

46
00:01:36,359 --> 00:01:37,239
Yeah, that's me.

47
00:01:37,239 --> 00:01:39,039
You might be wondering how I got here.

48
00:01:40,439 --> 00:01:44,960
Thea, you take 31.

49
00:01:44,960 --> 00:01:45,920
Oh no.

50
00:01:45,920 --> 00:01:47,159
Points of damage.

51
00:01:47,159 --> 00:01:49,799
New Lara, I think you're gonna shatter.

52
00:01:49,799 --> 00:01:51,519
I think so too.

53
00:01:51,519 --> 00:01:54,760
New Lara, so you take 60 damage.

54
00:01:54,760 --> 00:01:56,000
Oh my God.

55
00:01:56,000 --> 00:01:59,680
It looks like he's attempting to make an escape.

56
00:01:59,680 --> 00:02:02,920
All right, well, since I'm next to New Lara,

57
00:02:02,920 --> 00:02:05,280
I will try and stabilize New Lara.

58
00:02:05,280 --> 00:02:07,120
So that is 16.

59
00:02:07,120 --> 00:02:09,360
So she is also stabilized.

60
00:02:09,360 --> 00:02:12,840
Part of me wants to continue after the dragons.

61
00:02:12,840 --> 00:02:14,599
I feel like if we let him go now,

62
00:02:14,599 --> 00:02:15,800
we're gonna lose the trail.

63
00:02:15,800 --> 00:02:19,520
What you see in the cavern is a chute

64
00:02:19,520 --> 00:02:21,840
that descends down into the ocean,

65
00:02:21,840 --> 00:02:23,599
frigid waters of the ocean.

66
00:02:23,599 --> 00:02:25,520
There's a spell I can light the ocean on fire.

67
00:02:25,680 --> 00:02:27,480
Is there a spell you could light the ocean on fire?

68
00:02:27,480 --> 00:02:28,320
Yes. No.

69
00:02:28,320 --> 00:02:29,159
No.

70
00:02:29,159 --> 00:02:34,560
Well, hello, how are you today?

71
00:02:34,560 --> 00:02:35,600
That's great.

72
00:02:35,600 --> 00:02:37,240
Welcome to Dumbgeons and Dragons,

73
00:02:37,240 --> 00:02:40,680
a D&D fifth edition actual play podcast.

74
00:02:40,680 --> 00:02:42,760
I'm your dungeon master and co-host Russ More.

75
00:02:42,760 --> 00:02:45,120
Not with me today are Carla Johnson,

76
00:02:45,120 --> 00:02:46,800
who plays New Lara Moonbrook,

77
00:02:46,800 --> 00:02:49,200
Tom Laird, who plays Flint Firebeard,

78
00:02:49,200 --> 00:02:52,280
and my wife Amy More, who plays Thea Amastasia.

79
00:02:52,280 --> 00:02:54,800
Together, we are creating a world and a story

80
00:02:54,800 --> 00:02:56,160
for you to come along with.

81
00:02:56,160 --> 00:02:58,320
Take part in and enjoy for what it is,

82
00:02:58,320 --> 00:03:00,040
a dive into a fictional universe

83
00:03:00,040 --> 00:03:02,400
where adventure, intrigue, and excitement

84
00:03:02,400 --> 00:03:05,400
all come together and make a sweet, sweet, delicious

85
00:03:05,400 --> 00:03:08,120
Hot Pocket-style narrative podcast.

86
00:03:08,120 --> 00:03:08,960
Too much?

87
00:03:08,960 --> 00:03:11,240
Well, let's get to the reason

88
00:03:11,240 --> 00:03:13,439
we're breaking format a bit today.

89
00:03:13,439 --> 00:03:17,360
It starts with some good news and some bad news.

90
00:03:17,360 --> 00:03:20,000
The good news is you probably noticed

91
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:23,120
you have two new episodes in your download queue from us.

92
00:03:23,120 --> 00:03:23,960
Woo-hoo!

93
00:03:25,400 --> 00:03:28,759
The bad news is the reason for those two episodes.

94
00:03:28,759 --> 00:03:30,480
This episode, episode seven,

95
00:03:30,480 --> 00:03:33,159
now titled The Lost Dice Game,

96
00:03:33,159 --> 00:03:35,240
was lost to the tech gremlins

97
00:03:35,240 --> 00:03:37,840
that decided to jack with some audio,

98
00:03:37,840 --> 00:03:40,640
making it unrecognizable as conversation.

99
00:03:40,640 --> 00:03:43,520
And I couldn't put you through that.

100
00:03:43,520 --> 00:03:45,879
It just didn't sound very good at all.

101
00:03:45,879 --> 00:03:47,480
So here's what we're gonna do instead.

102
00:03:47,480 --> 00:03:49,000
I'm gonna give you a rundown

103
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:50,920
of the major plot points that were missed

104
00:03:50,920 --> 00:03:51,920
in this episode.

105
00:03:52,080 --> 00:03:55,440
And then we're gonna move right along to the next one.

106
00:03:55,440 --> 00:03:57,160
So let's get started.

107
00:03:57,160 --> 00:03:59,640
Fortunately, this was a bit of a decompressed period

108
00:03:59,640 --> 00:04:01,000
for our adventurers.

109
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:02,480
Flint, Thea, and Nularaaa

110
00:04:02,480 --> 00:04:04,680
lugged their treasures back on board the frost skimmer

111
00:04:04,680 --> 00:04:06,200
and set sail towards Luskin

112
00:04:06,200 --> 00:04:07,680
to return Makoth the Crimson

113
00:04:07,680 --> 00:04:10,840
and all the stolen wares to the Arcane Brotherhood

114
00:04:10,840 --> 00:04:12,400
in hopes of signing them on board

115
00:04:12,400 --> 00:04:14,560
to battle against the Cult of the Dragons.

116
00:04:14,560 --> 00:04:17,080
To begin, the adventurers take a long rest

117
00:04:17,080 --> 00:04:20,920
to regain much-needed HP, hit dice, and spell slots

118
00:04:20,920 --> 00:04:23,439
that were lost in their battle with Aruthatar.

119
00:04:23,439 --> 00:04:25,080
When they finish that, though,

120
00:04:25,080 --> 00:04:26,680
we resolve some of the special items

121
00:04:26,680 --> 00:04:29,000
that they used plot points for

122
00:04:29,000 --> 00:04:32,920
at the end of the dragon battle episode

123
00:04:32,920 --> 00:04:35,160
that they found when they were digging out treasure.

124
00:04:35,160 --> 00:04:36,840
Thea is now in possession

125
00:04:36,840 --> 00:04:39,800
of two functional Arrows of Dragonslaying,

126
00:04:39,800 --> 00:04:41,040
where the dragon being attacked

127
00:04:41,040 --> 00:04:44,920
must make a DC 17 Constitution saving throw

128
00:04:44,920 --> 00:04:48,840
or take an extra 6d10 piercing damage,

129
00:04:48,840 --> 00:04:50,759
half of that on a success.

130
00:04:50,800 --> 00:04:52,920
Flint has two wonderfully magical

131
00:04:52,920 --> 00:04:54,480
ice fragmentation grenades

132
00:04:54,480 --> 00:04:58,360
that have a 60-foot range and a 20-foot blast radius.

133
00:04:58,360 --> 00:05:00,279
Each creature within that radius

134
00:05:00,279 --> 00:05:03,439
must make a DC 15 Dex saving throw,

135
00:05:03,439 --> 00:05:05,680
taking 5d6 piercing damage

136
00:05:05,680 --> 00:05:08,240
plus 2d4 cold damage on a fail,

137
00:05:08,240 --> 00:05:10,079
half on a success.

138
00:05:10,079 --> 00:05:11,879
Nularaaa spent some of her time

139
00:05:11,879 --> 00:05:13,920
after her rest with Makoth the Crimson

140
00:05:13,920 --> 00:05:16,959
to learn a new spell from one of the spell books

141
00:05:16,959 --> 00:05:19,759
found within the Arcane Brotherhood stuff.

142
00:05:19,759 --> 00:05:22,360
She learned a spell called Boomerang Quiver.

143
00:05:22,360 --> 00:05:24,719
It's a second-level transmutation

144
00:05:24,719 --> 00:05:26,879
with a casting time of one bonus action

145
00:05:26,879 --> 00:05:30,519
requiring verbal and somatic or gesturing components

146
00:05:30,519 --> 00:05:34,159
and will last through concentration up to one hour.

147
00:05:34,159 --> 00:05:36,399
When Nularaaa casts this spell on a quiver,

148
00:05:36,399 --> 00:05:38,279
any Arrows removed from that quiver

149
00:05:38,279 --> 00:05:39,800
that do not find their target

150
00:05:39,800 --> 00:05:43,199
return to the quiver by the beginning of the next turn.

151
00:05:43,199 --> 00:05:44,480
During this training montage

152
00:05:44,480 --> 00:05:45,879
that Nularaaa had with Makoth,

153
00:05:45,879 --> 00:05:47,920
Makoth mentions that she senses

154
00:05:47,920 --> 00:05:50,160
Nularaaa has exceptional skill

155
00:05:50,160 --> 00:05:52,480
in more ways than she knows,

156
00:05:52,480 --> 00:05:54,759
to which Nularaaa said,

157
00:05:54,759 --> 00:05:56,240
"'Well, thank you.'"

158
00:05:56,240 --> 00:05:58,600
And that's where it was left.

159
00:05:58,600 --> 00:06:00,040
After looking at their goodies,

160
00:06:00,040 --> 00:06:02,520
Flint, Thea, and Nularaaa head down to the galley

161
00:06:02,520 --> 00:06:04,600
where there are some of the shipmates

162
00:06:04,600 --> 00:06:05,759
playing a dice game.

163
00:06:05,759 --> 00:06:06,800
And I'll let you know,

164
00:06:06,800 --> 00:06:09,240
the technical difficulties might have saved you

165
00:06:09,240 --> 00:06:10,240
from having to listen to me

166
00:06:10,240 --> 00:06:12,960
try to describe a dice game over Skype

167
00:06:12,960 --> 00:06:16,319
and everyone just not do well at it.

168
00:06:16,319 --> 00:06:18,399
Long story short, they lost some money

169
00:06:18,399 --> 00:06:20,240
and went to have some grog.

170
00:06:20,240 --> 00:06:22,839
Flint challenged a half-orc named Baran

171
00:06:22,839 --> 00:06:27,120
to an arm wrestle and beat him handily many times.

172
00:06:27,120 --> 00:06:29,120
Needless to say, Baran was quite embarrassed

173
00:06:29,120 --> 00:06:31,879
but used this opportunity to approach Flint

174
00:06:31,879 --> 00:06:34,959
and ask for assistance with what he describes

175
00:06:34,959 --> 00:06:38,719
as a cult problem in his hometown of Little Rock.

176
00:06:38,719 --> 00:06:41,480
Baran tells Flint that he and his sister Sasha

177
00:06:41,480 --> 00:06:44,279
escaped Little Rock and describes wearers of purple

178
00:06:44,280 --> 00:06:45,920
having come into his town

179
00:06:45,920 --> 00:06:47,960
and terrorizing the people in Little Rock

180
00:06:47,960 --> 00:06:51,000
for seemingly no other reason than to cause havoc.

181
00:06:51,000 --> 00:06:53,320
Flint tells Baran that he will have to discuss

182
00:06:53,320 --> 00:06:54,960
with Thea and Nularaaa,

183
00:06:54,960 --> 00:06:56,240
but this is likely something

184
00:06:56,240 --> 00:06:58,080
that they'll be able to help out with.

185
00:06:58,080 --> 00:07:00,720
Nularaaa is approached again by Makoth in the galley

186
00:07:00,720 --> 00:07:02,080
and taken aside.

187
00:07:02,080 --> 00:07:05,880
Makoth warns Nularaaa that Luskin is a very prejudicial

188
00:07:05,880 --> 00:07:07,880
and racially charged city.

189
00:07:07,880 --> 00:07:11,040
And while Thea and Flint will likely be able to pass

190
00:07:11,040 --> 00:07:13,360
about the docks of Luskin with little issue,

191
00:07:13,360 --> 00:07:16,319
they might not be as welcomed in the city.

192
00:07:16,319 --> 00:07:19,439
Makoth suggests that Nularaaa enters Luskin with her alone

193
00:07:19,439 --> 00:07:22,040
to return the stolen goods and sway the leaders

194
00:07:22,040 --> 00:07:24,879
of the Arcane Brotherhood to their cause.

195
00:07:24,879 --> 00:07:26,879
Thea, Flint and Nularaaa all come together

196
00:07:26,879 --> 00:07:29,120
to discuss Baran and Sasha's problems

197
00:07:29,120 --> 00:07:30,520
as well as Makoth's concerns

198
00:07:30,520 --> 00:07:32,800
about Thea and Flint entering Luskin

199
00:07:32,800 --> 00:07:34,800
to meet with the Arcane Brotherhood.

200
00:07:34,800 --> 00:07:37,000
After much debate about splitting the party,

201
00:07:37,000 --> 00:07:38,600
they decide to tell Makoth

202
00:07:38,600 --> 00:07:41,319
that she must do what she can to convince the Brotherhood

203
00:07:41,319 --> 00:07:43,160
to fight against the Cult of the Dragon

204
00:07:43,160 --> 00:07:45,680
while the three of them go off to Little Rock

205
00:07:45,680 --> 00:07:47,520
and help the people there.

206
00:07:47,520 --> 00:07:49,680
When they return, they will meet with Makoth

207
00:07:49,680 --> 00:07:52,200
and any other representatives of the Arcane Brotherhood

208
00:07:52,200 --> 00:07:54,840
and discuss options further if needed.

209
00:07:54,840 --> 00:07:56,040
Once they arrive in Luskin,

210
00:07:56,040 --> 00:07:58,280
the three send Makoth through the gates of Luskin

211
00:07:58,280 --> 00:08:00,400
and head off with Baran and Sasha

212
00:08:00,400 --> 00:08:02,480
after renting a carriage of horses.

213
00:08:02,480 --> 00:08:04,680
Little Rock is located approximately halfway

214
00:08:04,680 --> 00:08:06,680
between Luskin and Mirabar

215
00:08:06,680 --> 00:08:09,879
and they expect to arrive within one to two days.

216
00:08:09,879 --> 00:08:12,560
On the road, the adventurers come across a band of dwarves

217
00:08:12,560 --> 00:08:14,600
who appear to have taken a wear of purple

218
00:08:14,600 --> 00:08:16,519
with the Cult of Dragons prisoner.

219
00:08:16,519 --> 00:08:19,519
After some negotiation and payment to the dwarves,

220
00:08:19,519 --> 00:08:21,079
they question this woman

221
00:08:21,079 --> 00:08:24,040
who they find out is named Chila Flagsteel.

222
00:08:24,040 --> 00:08:25,759
They learn that she got a little too greedy

223
00:08:25,759 --> 00:08:27,199
while leading a group of cultists

224
00:08:27,199 --> 00:08:29,160
that was terrorizing the dwarves.

225
00:08:29,160 --> 00:08:32,279
Some super tough negotiations and banter happens

226
00:08:32,279 --> 00:08:35,039
and the adventurers learn of a lead from Chila.

227
00:08:35,039 --> 00:08:36,679
They learn that one of the worm-speakers,

228
00:08:36,679 --> 00:08:38,600
Nerenvain, has gone missing from the cult

229
00:08:38,600 --> 00:08:40,600
and is heard to have fortified a stronghold

230
00:08:40,600 --> 00:08:42,080
in the Misty Forest.

231
00:08:42,120 --> 00:08:44,840
He may even be trying to defect from the Cult of the Dragon,

232
00:08:44,840 --> 00:08:47,040
but who's to say either way

233
00:08:47,040 --> 00:08:49,360
until you talk to someone, right?

234
00:08:49,360 --> 00:08:51,759
As the adventurers go to hand Chila back over,

235
00:08:51,759 --> 00:08:53,759
the dwarves are struck by a large boulder

236
00:08:53,759 --> 00:08:55,879
and the adventurers turn to see four ogres

237
00:08:55,879 --> 00:08:57,360
charging towards them.

238
00:08:57,360 --> 00:08:59,120
The dwarves turn tail and run,

239
00:08:59,120 --> 00:09:01,680
but the adventurers charge to fight the ogres.

240
00:09:01,680 --> 00:09:03,200
That's the end of the episode.

241
00:09:03,200 --> 00:09:04,840
Quite a lot covered there.

242
00:09:04,840 --> 00:09:06,759
Thanks for listening through this one.

243
00:09:06,759 --> 00:09:08,520
There is another episode right away

244
00:09:08,520 --> 00:09:10,920
so you can have the full adventure experience

245
00:09:10,919 --> 00:09:12,039
with all four of us,

246
00:09:12,039 --> 00:09:15,159
but there was just too much that was touched on

247
00:09:15,159 --> 00:09:17,360
to just avoid it altogether.

248
00:09:17,360 --> 00:09:18,679
You can keep those reviews coming in.

249
00:09:18,679 --> 00:09:20,479
We love hearing what you think about the show.

250
00:09:20,479 --> 00:09:22,039
It really does mean a whole lot to us

251
00:09:22,039 --> 00:09:23,759
when you tell us what you think.

252
00:09:23,759 --> 00:09:24,959
You can head over to iTunes

253
00:09:24,959 --> 00:09:26,799
and leave your review and rating.

254
00:09:26,799 --> 00:09:28,079
The ratings are great,

255
00:09:28,079 --> 00:09:29,439
but the reviews along with them

256
00:09:29,439 --> 00:09:31,599
help a little bit more, I think,

257
00:09:31,599 --> 00:09:33,240
because it tells someone who's cruising around

258
00:09:33,240 --> 00:09:34,679
looking for a podcast to listen to

259
00:09:34,679 --> 00:09:37,319
that this one may be worth their time.

260
00:09:37,319 --> 00:09:39,079
You can also tell your friends, family,

261
00:09:39,160 --> 00:09:41,680
or your next door neighbor to visit DumbDragons.com.

